      "text": "JL: One task is also supported by one script.\nOne Script support one task, with many many different configurations",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "JL: One task is also supported by one script.\nOne Script support one task, with many many different configurations",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "4qhqZjUQbneUOrhjB-Ceg",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1750,
      "y": 200,
      "width": 1080,
      "height": 1836,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#9c36b5",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aq",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1677926036,
      "version": 11,
      "versionNonce": 1992767854,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777224601705,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "CC: 🧠 Mental model — Project ⊃ Task ⊃ Run\n\nEach level is bound by ONE distinct predicate\n(synthesizes your red notes #5, #6, #7, #8):\n\n  📦 PROJECT  bound by  AIM\n                        ─────\n        your #5: \"research topic + aim\"\n        e.g. \"model SMS engagement\", \"test-to-learn protocol\"\n\n  🧩 TASK     bound by  SCRIPT\n                        ──────\n        your #7,#8: \"one script supports one task\n                     with many configurations\"\n        one .py driver / one .sh template / one logic;\n        fans out into N runs.\n\n  ⚙️ RUN      bound by  CONFIG\n                        ──────\n        your #6: \"one .sh + one yaml + one results folder\"\n        one execution; reproducible from config alone.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nOne-line summary:\n\n  A run is one config;\n  a task is one script;\n  a project is one aim.\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nThe 1:1:1 inside a task (run level):\n\n  config/X.yaml  ←→  runs/X.sh  ←→  results/X/\n        │                │              │\n        └─ varies ───────┴── shares ────┘\n           per run         driver .py\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nBoundary smell tests:\n\n  • Two configs need DIFFERENT scripts\n                      → split into 2 tasks\n  • Two tasks share NO research question\n                      → split into 2 projects\n  • Project has only 1 task\n                      → it's a task, not a project\n  • \"Task\" runs once with no variants\n                      → fold into parent task\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nWhere each lives in the tree:\n\n  RUN     → tasks/{G}_{S}_group/{T}_task/\n            {config|runs|sbatch|results}/X.*\n  TASK    → tasks/{G}_{S}_group/{T}_task/\n            (folder + diagram/)\n  PROJECT → examples/{Proj}/\n            (folder + diagram/ + paper/)\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nProposed actions on the .txt sources:\n\n  ① Add this mental-model § to 01-shape.txt\n     (right after Top-level layout)\n  ② Lift boundary smell-tests into\n     02-task-internals.txt §2\n  ③ Bake rename-and-share convention into §5\n     ({level}-XX-YYMMDD.excalidraw)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "CC: 🧠 Mental model — Project ⊃ Task ⊃ Run\n\nEach level is bound by ONE distinct predicate\n(synthesizes your red notes #5, #6, #7, #8):\n\n  📦 PROJECT  bound by  AIM\n                        ─────\n        your #5: \"research topic + aim\"\n        e.g. \"model SMS engagement\", \"test-to-learn protocol\"\n\n  🧩 TASK     bound by  SCRIPT\n                        ──────\n        your #7,#8: \"one script supports one task\n                     with many configurations\"\n        one .py driver / one .sh template / one logic;\n        fans out into N runs.\n\n  ⚙️ RUN      bound by  CONFIG\n                        ──────\n        your #6: \"one .sh + one yaml + one results folder\"\n        one execution; reproducible from config alone.\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nOne-line summary:\n\n  A run is one config;\n  a task is one script;\n  a project is one aim.\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nThe 1:1:1 inside a task (run level):\n\n  config/X.yaml  ←→  runs/X.sh  ←→  results/X/\n        │                │              │\n        └─ varies ───────┴── shares ────┘\n           per run         driver .py\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nBoundary smell tests:\n\n  • Two configs need DIFFERENT scripts\n                      → split into 2 tasks\n  • Two tasks share NO research question\n                      → split into 2 projects\n  • Project has only 1 task\n                      → it's a task, not a project\n  • \"Task\" runs once with no variants\n                      → fold into parent task\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nWhere each lives in the tree:\n\n  RUN     → tasks/{G}_{S}_group/{T}_task/\n            {config|runs|sbatch|results}/X.*\n  TASK    → tasks/{G}_{S}_group/{T}_task/\n            (folder + diagram/)\n  PROJECT → examples/{Proj}/\n            (folder + diagram/ + paper/)\n\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nProposed actions on the .txt sources:\n\n  ① Add this mental-model § to 01-shape.txt\n     (right after Top-level layout)\n  ② Lift boundary smell-tests into\n     02-task-internals.txt §2\n  ③ Bake rename-and-share convention into §5\n     ({level}-XX-YYMMDD.excalidraw)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "Tlo9EC331CrBnhRYRYMc2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 899.8418101247354,
      "y": 1755.3340870960683,
      "width": 322.81302429061225,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#9c36b5",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ar",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 128648660,
      "version": 113,
      "versionNonce": 1972901746,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777224652097,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "CC: 🧩 Task content = ONE\nscript + its config sweep + a\ndiagram/.\n   contents = config/ + runs/ +\nsbatch/ + results/ + diagram/ +\n*.py\n   The script (.py) is the\ninvariant; configs vary it;\ndiagram/\n   captures WHY those configs\nand the conclusion across them.\n   → See mental-model panel\n(top-left) — task is bounded by\nSCRIPT.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "CC: 🧩 Task content = ONE script + its config sweep + a diagram/.\n   contents = config/ + runs/ + sbatch/ + results/ + diagram/ + *.py\n   The script (.py) is the invariant; configs vary it; diagram/\n   captures WHY those configs and the conclusion across them.\n   → See mental-model panel (top-left) — task is bounded by SCRIPT.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "QHEqOtkGk4s6KepmHVzSH",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1995.8358651251,
      "y": 1909.5526205412502,
      "width": 339.5546721132105,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#9c36b5",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
